<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Gear Corridor</h3>

    <p>Beyond the glass walls, clockwork machines click and hum. Bronze gears tick in their gearshafts. On the ceiling, liquid rushes through glass pipes, occasionally leaking onto the floor where the pipes have cracked. Darkly shimmering amber fluid accumulates in small pools.</p>

    <p>The corridor runs [[north|nexusDome]] and <a class="panelOpener" identifier="south">sou%�MN</a>. A sliding glass door, thick enough that you can see barely anything beyond, leads [[east|bathhouse]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="glassTowerStairwell" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Glass Tower - Stairwell</h3>

    <p>The stairs are hovering blocks of glass, spiraling [[up|glassTowerSummit]] the tower. Glass orbs cycle through the air, some cracked, drizzling amber fluid. A small amber pool has accumulated at the bottom of the stairwell.</p>

    <p>Steps to the [[west|indicatorCorridorQuantitative]] lead out, into a metal corridor.</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="glassTowerSummit" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Glass Tower - Summit</h3>

    <p>A glass dome at the pinnacle of the glass tower. Through the windows you see other towers, other castles. Or perhaps just one castle duplicated across all available space, the same towers repeating infinitely into the distance, forever. A <a class="whiteMarker bronzeSlab">bronze slab</a> leans against the wall.</p>

    <p>The only way out is [[down|glassTowerStairwell]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="diningHall" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Dining Hall</h3>

    <p>An enormous room, most of which is taken up by a long table covered in rich velvet tablecloth. Gilt chairs, straight-backed and elegant, line the table. The velvet tablecloth boasts a panoply of dishes and platters and cups, but instead of food, all they hold is a glittering amber liquid. On some plates it bubbles. On others it sizzles. But there is nothing edible here.</p>

    <p>An oaken door to the [[west|indicatorCorridorQuantitative]] leads out. A small metal door is situated to the [[south|novumInstrumentum]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="clockLounge" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Clock Lounge</h3>

    <p>A lounge of some kind. Rich red carpet, plush rugs, plush sofas, and gently ticking clocks covering the walls. A fireplace burns bright, and to its side, a bronze slab glimmers.</p>

    <p>An enormous clock on one wall has elegant wrought-iron hands behind a shining glass face and gilt paneling. The clock is stopped at five minutes to midnight.</p>

    <p>An elegant wooden door inlaid with glass and copper leads [[west|indicatorCorridorQualitative]], back to the corridor.</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="novumInstrumentum" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Novum Instrumentum</h3>

    <p>Most of this comparatively tiny room is occupied by an enormous clockwork contraption, a hulk of a machine sporting bronze gears and steam hissing out from pipes and release valves and all kinds of indicators and lights. It is cracked down the center, exposing a mass of metal scraps and twisted black wires that erupt with the occasional bursts of orange sparks. You can see no way to interface with the machine.</p>

    <p>A small metal door leads [[north|diningHall]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="sinkhouse" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Sinkhouse</h3>

    <p>Sinks of various heights and sizes rise around you, an artificial forest. Amber fluid trickles into basins of porcelain and copper and steel, and drops of amber cover the white tiles on the floor. Pipes trace erratic patterns along the walls.</p>

    <p>A thick sliding glass door, behind which you can see glimmers of multicolored light, leads [[west|nexusDome]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="bathhouse" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Bathhouse</h3>

    <p>The floor is pitted with pools of various shapes, containing various liquids. There are circular pools of water, but also liquids of white, blue, amber. Pools that shimmer and ripple and pools encrusted by a thin layer of frost and pools that radiate heat, from which colored smoke wafts. Spotlights above sway, dappling the walls with refracted light.</p>

    <p>The room darkens to the [[east|bathhouseDeepWater]]. A sliding glass door, thick enough that you can see barely anything beyond, leads [[west|gearCorridor]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="bathhouseDeepWater" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Bathhouse - Deep Water</h3>

    <p>At the far end of this room is an enormous pool of water, frothing and bubbling. The lights are dim here, and between the darkness and the depth of the water, it is impossible to tell where the bottom is. Strong currents make it impossible to dive in without being pushed back to the surface.</p>

    <p>The room brightens to the [[west|bathhouse]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="redLounge1" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Red Lounge</h3>

    <p>Rich red carpet. A delicate wooden chair sits before a glass-topped table, engraved with a spiraling pattern. Creamy off-white walls. Glass chandeliers hang from a high ceiling crossed with oaken beams.</p>

    <p>A nondescript wooden door leads to the [[east|redLounge2]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="redLounge2" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Red Lounge</h3>

    <p>Creamy off-white carpet. A red plastic lawn chair sits before a copper table engraved with a spiraling pattern. Deep red walls. Chandeliers of red glass hang from a high ceiling crossed with oaken beams.</p>

    <p>A nondescript wooden door leads to the [[east|redLounge3]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="redLounge3" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Red Lounge</h3>

    <p>Rich red carpet. A delicate glass chair sits before a plastic table surrounded by plastic walls. Wooden chandeliers hang from a high ceiling crossed with glass beams.</p>

    <p>A nondescript copper door leads to the [[east|redLounge4]].</p>
</div>

</snippet>

<snippet name="redLounge4" scripts="meta/markerDivScript.js">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Red Lounge</h3>

    <p>Glass carpet cuts at your feet. The chair, walls, and table are covered in soft red fuzz. There is no ceiling, or it is so high above that you can't see it.</p>

    <p>A red door leads to the east.</p>
</div>

</snippet>
